The paper analyzes the coverage of Microsoft Academic in comparison to Scopus and Web of Science, which are databases commonly used in bibliometrics. The study focuses on the level of individual publications and citation counts, which suggests that the paper is likely to fall under the categories of digital libraries (cs.DL) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Additionally, the study involves the use of a Perl script for data retrieval, which could also place it under the category of cybernetics (cs.CY). The analysis of biases in coverage could also relate to the category of machine learning (cs.LG), as it involves identifying patterns and trends in data.
